abstract: >-
  Research software for image inverse problems that combines a learned
  encoder-generator initialization with an image-space Recurrent Inference
  Machine. The implementation evaluates single-pixel imaging and
  super-resolution on MNIST against GANI, EADMM, PEADMM, and a standard RIM.
keywords:
  - inverse problems
  - recurrent inference machines
  - generative priors
  - single-pixel imaging
  - super-resolution
  - PyTorch
